    mainPoints:
      "Key Points:\n\n1. Absolute value is denoted by two vertical bars surrounding a number, e.g., |x|.\n2. The absolute value of a positive number is the number itself.\n3. The absolute value of a negative number is its positive counterpart.\n4. The absolute value of zero is zero.",
